1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,882
[objects rustling and clattering]

2
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:09,843
[woman] Huh? What?

3
00:00:12,762 --> 00:00:14,848
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

4
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:19,144
Where's the rest of it?

5
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:26,109
[intriguing music playing]

6
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,144
[exhales]

7
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:07,192
[sighs]

8
00:01:09,778 --> 00:01:11,571
Not here. Shit.

9
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:14,491
[sighs]

10
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:18,036
Fujita!

11
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:20,455
Fujita!

12
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:22,791
[Fujita] Yeah?

13
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:27,420
[woman] 21,500 yen.

14
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:30,924
- [Fujita] What?
- [woman] It's gone.

15
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:32,509
Where'd you put the money?

16
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:39,057
Hey, don't worry. It was a…

17
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:41,226
- An investment.
- What?

18
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,479
- Don't tell me it's gone?
- Kaho…

19
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:46,314
I…

20
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:51,069
I think I found something
way better than a few thousand yen.

21
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:53,780
[Kaho] Hmm?

22
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:00,537
A collection of music videos
from an idol group.

23
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:04,082
Underground, unknown,
called Dream Succubus.

24
00:02:04,165 --> 00:02:05,792
TAX INCLUDED PRICE ¥21,500

25
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,293
[Kaho] Are you serious?

26
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:09,963
You took the money for this?

27
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:13,716
The plan was to save up
and buy a new camera!

28
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,176
[coins rattling in tin]

29
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,305
- Mm-hmm.
- [Kaho sighs]

30
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:22,642
- Trust me. You'll wanna see this.
- [Kaho] What? Why?

31
00:02:22,725 --> 00:02:24,644
[Fujita chuckles] Come on.

32
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:27,522
[Kaho] I'm gonna straight-up murder you.

33
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:30,316
They'll execute me for it,
like <i>Dancer in the Dark.</i>

34
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,276
[Fujita chuckles]

35
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:36,072
DREAM SUCCUBUS

36
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:39,367
[pop music playing over speakers]

37
00:02:46,457 --> 00:02:47,500
[Kaho scoffs]

38
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:49,502
Oof.

39
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:51,880
I guess I gotta ask,

40
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:54,507
are you, like,
into this kinda stuff now or you--

41
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:55,758
It's not like that.

42
00:02:56,259 --> 00:02:58,178
This music video was directed by Goro.

43
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:00,638
I like his work, so I bought it, and then…

44
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:06,311
- Ah.
- [music pauses]

45
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:08,229
Right there. There.

46
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,773
Wait. Hey. No.

47
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:12,609
- Look.
- [Kaho] What?

48
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:14,861
[Fujita] Look. There.

49
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,447
[hopeful string music playing]

50
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,872
[Kaho] Wait. Is that…

51
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:29,876
Great day for believers.

52
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:32,295
Kaho…

53
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,008
We found it after searching for so long.

54
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:40,470
We're one step closer
to finding the Human Vapor.

55
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,640
What no one's ever done before.

56
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,602
[music becomes mysterious]

57
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:52,023
The Human Vapor.

58
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:55,068
It's gotta be.

59
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:58,404
[Fujita singing]

60
00:03:58,488 --> 00:03:59,572
[Kaho grunts]

61
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:02,033
[Kaho] No, no, come on, look up.

62
00:04:02,116 --> 00:04:04,577
- Stop that. I'll take your eye out.
- [Fujita singing]

63
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:07,288
- We've gotta start. C'mon. Go.
- No, I'm not done.

64
00:04:07,372 --> 00:04:10,667
It's already nine o'clock.
We go live in five. My fans are waiting.

65
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:13,753
Four, three, two…

66
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:17,882
LIVE

67
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,385
<i>Welcome to horror paradise!</i>

68
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,554
<i>Hi! We're back again</i>
<i>with </i>Fujita and Kaho's Terror Zone.

69
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,390
<i>- I'm Fujita.</i>
- [Kaho] <i>And I'm Kaho!</i>

70
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:27,058
<i>How are you killers tonight?</i>

71
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:28,935
<i>You ready to be terrified?</i>

72
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,020
<i>Of course you are, right?</i>

73
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,189
<i>Because you all know</i>
<i>what we're about to share</i>

74
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:34,899
<i>is guaranteed to mess you up.</i>

75
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:37,694
<i>Our videos will have you</i>
<i>shaking in your boots!</i>

76
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:39,028
<i>Huh?</i>

77
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:41,698
<i>Or whatever shoes you've got on!</i>

78
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:43,533
[Kaho] <i>Drop the footwear</i>
<i>and get to the point!</i>

79
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:45,868
Go on, quick. The main event.

80
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,622
Main event.

81
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:51,582
Tonight.

82
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:54,794
Now I bet you know
what we're talking about.

83
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:56,587
It's everywhere you look.

84
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,381
Let me hear you say it…

85
00:04:58,464 --> 00:05:00,466
[curious music playing]

86
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:03,428
You're so right.

87
00:05:03,928 --> 00:05:05,471
The Human Vapor.

88
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:06,681
[chuckles softly]

89
00:05:06,764 --> 00:05:09,142
[Fujita] Enough theatrics!
You saw the announcement.

90
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:12,770
Now you're here for the goods,
super rare footage that will reveal,

91
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:15,982
once and for all,
the true identity of the Human Vapor,

92
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:18,026
here on <i>Fujita and Kaho's Terror Zone!</i>

93
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:21,321
[yells excitedly]

94
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:26,159
<i>Oh, I hope you're ready</i>
<i>for the scare of your life!</i>

95
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:29,037
<i>Kaho… roll it!</i>

96
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:33,166
[dramatic drumbeats]

97
00:05:33,249 --> 00:05:35,835
[pop music playing]

98
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:43,426
- I don't get it.
- [Kaho sighs]

99
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:46,763
- I'm serious. It doesn't make sense.
- [Kaho sighs]

100
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:50,224
I figured we'd crack at least 100 viewers.

101
00:05:50,308 --> 00:05:51,434
[Kaho chuckles]

102
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:53,603
Seven isn't quite 100, you're right.

103
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:56,064
[chuckles] So what do we do now?

104
00:05:58,608 --> 00:05:59,484
[Kaho chuckles]

105
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,153
Here, close your eyes.

106
00:06:02,236 --> 00:06:03,654
[Fujita sighs] Come on.

107
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:05,239
- Close your eyes.
- Okay.

108
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:12,663
- Kaho, maybe it's time for you to host--
- No, I already told you.

109
00:06:12,747 --> 00:06:14,540
[gentle piano music playing]

110
00:06:14,624 --> 00:06:15,708
It's just…

111
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,046
You're just, like…

112
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:24,133
You're way more beautiful
than you think you are, Kaho.

113
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:25,551
Do you know that?

114
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,428
Ah, ah, ah! Ah!

115
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:28,846
Stop, that hurts!

116
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,181
So, hey…

117
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:34,394
You know if this keeps up,
there's no way we're gonna make it.

118
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:35,770
[both chuckle]

119
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,647
Ow, that stings, stop! Ah!

120
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,232
- [Kaho laughs]
- Ow.

121
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:40,775
- Sorry.
- [phone buzzes]

122
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,696
- Whoa, look at this. Right here.
- [Kaho] Mm-hmm?

123
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:47,281
[Fujita] This is crazy, look.

124
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:52,286
[Kaho] What? Wait. Hey, hey. Look!

125
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:56,332
[Fujita] "@dadashow"

126
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,459
"I was very intrigued by today's video."

127
00:06:58,543 --> 00:07:01,587
"I would like to purchase
the details of your investigation."

128
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:02,672
What?

129
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:04,424
No way.

130
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:07,677
Is this real?

131
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,180
Uh, so should we…

132
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,141
at least, like, hear the offer?

133
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:14,934
- Yeah.
- Mm.

134
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:15,893
Yeah.

135
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:18,980
Okay, I'll… [chuckles]

136
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:22,358
[Kaho sighs happily]

137
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:31,200
I'm gonna send them my phone number.

138
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:35,496
If whoever this is reaches out
after that, then it's real.

139
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:39,667
[Fujita] Yo, Kaho. Take a look at this.

140
00:07:40,251 --> 00:07:41,919
Isn't this crazy cool? [chuckles]

141
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:43,671
- That's been there forever.
- Huh?

142
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:46,632
- Don't you remember? You found it.
- What? When?

143
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,301
I don't know for sure, but…

144
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,720
Mom was there.

145
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,974
- [Fujita] She was? Really?
- Yeah.

146
00:07:56,684 --> 00:07:57,810
[Kaho hums a tune]

147
00:07:57,894 --> 00:07:59,645
[phone vibrating]

148
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:00,730
[Fujita] Is that…

149
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,441
- Yeah. It's them.
- [Fujita] They're calling?

150
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,818
They're calling,
they're calling, they're calling!

151
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,405
Uh, hello?

152
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:13,159
Yes. This is Kaho
from <i>Fujita and Kaho's Terror Zone.</i>

153
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,370
Are you… are you "Dadashow?"

154
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,039
Uh-huh.

155
00:08:20,208 --> 00:08:23,336
[scoffs] Well, of course, it's real, yes.

156
00:08:24,128 --> 00:08:26,047
Yes, we looked into it.

157
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,093
The location of the building?

158
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:33,304
Uh…

159
00:08:33,387 --> 00:08:37,016
We can't release those details, sorry.

160
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:41,312
Well, that depends on how much.

161
00:08:42,438 --> 00:08:43,314
Yeah.

162
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:45,691
Huh?

163
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:48,694
- Sorry, a million?
- What? A million?

164
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:50,655
Uh… Sure.

165
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:52,782
Uh…

166
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:54,492
No. Uh, yes.

167
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,118
Right, of course.

168
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:59,080
Yeah. I understand, yes.

169
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,792
I do. No, no, no, that's completely fine.

170
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:04,293
Thank you, that's quite…

171
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:07,129
Oh. They're gone.

172
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:15,930
[Fujita chuckles]

173
00:09:18,182 --> 00:09:19,475
What did they say?

174
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:22,019
That they want it. For a million.

175
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:23,688
A million? You're serious?

176
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,565
- Yeah.
- Like, for real?

177
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:29,610
- Yeah, for real.
- Oh, it's happening! It's happening!

178
00:09:30,194 --> 00:09:31,696
We're actually doing it!

179
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:35,491
- Great day for believers.
- [Kaho laughs]

180
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,119
Great day for believers!

181
00:09:39,203 --> 00:09:40,329
[Fujita chuckles]

182
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,415
What did I tell you?!

183
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:43,833
[Kaho] Dadashow.

184
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,711
[Fujita laughs]

185
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:50,756
[dark, dramatic music playing]

186
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:32,632
HUMAN VAPOR

187
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:41,766
There can't be a production company here.
No way in hell.

188
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:45,561
Look, this is the best lead we've had
to find this place.

189
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:48,439
If anyone knows,
it'll be the company that made the video.

190
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,859
"In the Socks."

191
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:55,571
[gasps] There. Up there.

192
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,657
[whimsical string music playing]

193
00:11:13,839 --> 00:11:17,968
- [girl 1] My mom's not home right now.
- [girl 2] So we can do whatever we want.

194
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:19,637
[girl 1] Yeah!

195
00:11:20,137 --> 00:11:22,515
We could get some snacks
and play at the arcade!

196
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:34,151
[girl 2] Whoa. Did you see her face?
That, like, bruise thing?

197
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,490
[music fades out]

198
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:44,745
[Kaho, over phone] <i>Fujita?</i>

199
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:48,332
Just… be normal in there.
Don't say anything weird or whatever.

200
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:50,835
[Fujita] <i>Obviously. I know.</i>

201
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,003
[Kaho] Okay. Step one, knock.

202
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:55,589
[meowing inside]

203
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:58,134
[meowing continues]

204
00:11:58,217 --> 00:11:59,552
[meowing over phone]

205
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:00,720
What is that?

206
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:01,929
[meowing continues]

207
00:12:02,763 --> 00:12:05,891
[man] No, no, no, that's all wrong.
I need to see a cat, okay?

208
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:08,144
A real cat. A cat in heat.
Like you're trying to attract…

209
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:09,270
[Kaho] <i>Go in!</i>

210
00:12:09,353 --> 00:12:10,980
[woman meowing]

211
00:12:11,063 --> 00:12:14,150
[man] No, no, you're not listening!
I need you to really embody the cat.

212
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,736
Hey! That's… Cut. Cut! Cut, okay?

213
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:19,071
Imagine starting the meow like a siren.
A warning.

214
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:22,116
- [woman 1] Okay. I'll try.
- [man] Ready? And… action.

215
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:26,078
[woman 1 meows]

216
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:28,581
- [woman 2] Excuse me, who are you?
- Oh! Uh…

217
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:30,458
Well, I'm, uh… Uh…

218
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:33,127
- [Fujita] <i>Sorry, I…</i>
- [Kaho] Say you have an interview.

219
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:35,963
- [Kaho] <i>You saw the listing.</i>
- I saw the job listing on your…

220
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:36,964
[Kaho] <i>Website.</i>

221
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,217
I came to be the director's apprentice.

222
00:12:40,301 --> 00:12:42,178
[Kaho] <i>I told you not to improvise.</i>

223
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:44,346
- Do you have a resume?
- [Fujita] I, uh…

224
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,806
[woman 1 continues meowing]

225
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,808
[man] No. Cut!

226
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:52,354
RESUME
FUJITA FUJIKAWA

227
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,482
[Fujita] My name is Fujita Fujikawa.

228
00:13:01,113 --> 00:13:02,490
Mr. Goro, sir,

229
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:05,493
it's such an honor to meet you.

230
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,038
Can I just say

231
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:12,875
I am a huge fan of your work.
All of your work.

232
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:18,798
You are imitating my fashion.

233
00:13:31,268 --> 00:13:32,728
Who is this guy?

234
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:34,522
He's weird.

235
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,025
I'll do anything, sir.

236
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,529
- Do you know how to drive?
- Yes.

237
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:43,322
Can you work a tailgate lift?

238
00:13:43,405 --> 00:13:46,075
Of course,
and I have my color certification.

239
00:13:46,158 --> 00:13:47,576
Unnecessary.

240
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:55,084
Yesterday, what did you have for lunch?

241
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:57,711
[Fujita] A hamburger.

242
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:01,090
Your favorite ingredient
to add to miso soup?

243
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,591
I don't really like it.

244
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:04,802
- You ever hit another person?
- Never, sir.

245
00:14:04,885 --> 00:14:07,137
How old when you stopped bathing
with your mother?

246
00:14:09,265 --> 00:14:11,559
I don't really remember my mother.

247
00:14:14,895 --> 00:14:16,272
Languages you know?

248
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,815
Three, Mr. Goro.

249
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:20,693
- [Goro] What about German?
- I speak some.

250
00:14:20,776 --> 00:14:22,069
Then speak some.

251
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:28,868
Fujita, come on, do it. You have to.

252
00:14:34,957 --> 00:14:38,002
[meowing realistically]

253
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:45,801
[continues meowing]

254
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:53,350
[stops meowing]

255
00:15:08,198 --> 00:15:09,700
Right, you got this, buddy.

256
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:17,333
All this to say, uh,

257
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,835
I'm a big fan.

258
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,546
I love all your work, but, uh,

259
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:25,466
especially your music videos.

260
00:15:25,549 --> 00:15:28,385
There was one you did for Dream Succubus.

261
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:31,013
- Wagamama Nightmare.
- Wagamama Nightmare.

262
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:34,058
You shot it in a warehouse.

263
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,435
It blew me away.

264
00:15:36,518 --> 00:15:38,354
[chuckles awkwardly]

265
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:45,611
[knocking at door]

266
00:15:48,113 --> 00:15:50,157
Sorry to interrupt.

267
00:15:57,957 --> 00:15:59,166
[Goro] You should try it.

268
00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:02,836
<i>No one makes lemonade like she does.</i>

269
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,005
[Kaho] What?

270
00:16:06,256 --> 00:16:09,093
Wait a second.
That doesn't look like lemonade.

271
00:16:11,136 --> 00:16:12,638
What did she just give you?

272
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:15,140
[quirky percussive music playing]

273
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,811
[slurping]

274
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:20,896
[Fujita gulping]

275
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,034
How is it?

276
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:38,664
It's, um…

277
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:50,843
It's orange juice?

278
00:16:50,926 --> 00:16:52,511
[woman laughs]

279
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:54,430
What?

280
00:16:57,599 --> 00:16:58,934
What the…

281
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:07,317
So,

282
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,987
you passed the test.

283
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,907
In a world of lemonade sheep,

284
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,744
you saw the orange juice
and told the truth.

285
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:18,454
Welcome aboard.

286
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:25,044
Those oranges come from my hometown
in Ehime. I squeezed them myself.

287
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,716
With my bare hands.

288
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,636
[Goro] Isn't that marvelous?

289
00:17:35,304 --> 00:17:38,474
The human body is truly beyond compare.

290
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:42,186
A machine can't deliver
such exquisite taste.

291
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:49,068
The Wagamama Nightmare music video
was filmed in an abandoned warehouse.

292
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:50,069
Where is it?

293
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:51,945
I've always been curious, sir.

294
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:54,364
Oh, well,

295
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:57,743
the band's manager found it for us.
His name is Kenta.

296
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,996
Where is he now?
Is he still working as a manager?

297
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,915
[Goro] I don't know where he is.

298
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:08,087
He said something
about wanting to be an actor.

299
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:11,465
<i>I wouldn't put it past him.</i>
<i>He's a slippery one.</i>

300
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:14,009
[intriguing music playing]

301
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,136
[Kaho] <i>Hey, Fujita.</i>

302
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,846
<i>- That's Mimi.</i>
- What?

303
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,974
[Kaho] Mimi. She's part of Dream Succubus.

304
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:23,435
Maybe she can tell us.

305
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:26,146
Sorry, are you

306
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,857
Mimi from Dream Succubus?

307
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:31,193
Yeah.

308
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:38,158
Maybe you know… something
about what might've happened to Kenta?

309
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:43,038
No. I have no clue.

310
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,266
Yo, there. Look!

311
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:03,642
KENTA SUMERAGI

312
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:06,061
[Kaho] There he is. I knew it.

313
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,980
Yeah, good call.

314
00:19:15,028 --> 00:19:16,530
[music fades out]

315
00:19:16,613 --> 00:19:19,074
[Fujita] Come on, Kaho, let's get you
in there. Come on. Move.

316
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:20,784
- [Kaho] No, I told you.
- It's your turn.

317
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,078
[Kaho] You go in. Like you did with Goro.

318
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:26,165
No way! You know it would be weird
for a guy to go in there alone.

319
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:28,000
Wear a disguise then, I don't know.

320
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:30,460
[Fujita sighs]

321
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,839
Kaho.

322
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:37,885
Think of the money. Think about that.

323
00:19:39,386 --> 00:19:41,638
We see Kenta,
find out where the building is,

324
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:42,890
and we earn a million!

325
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:44,975
Yeah, I know, it's just that I…

326
00:19:46,810 --> 00:19:48,896
I don't want anyone to see how I look.

327
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,358
[sighs]

328
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:56,278
That's fine, yep!

329
00:19:56,987 --> 00:20:00,991
You just wanna go the rest of your life
only talking to me, only eating with me,

330
00:20:01,074 --> 00:20:02,701
and avoiding the rest of the world.

331
00:20:02,784 --> 00:20:05,913
It's not like that.
It's not like I chose this stupid face.

332
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:08,665
- Go to hell!
- I know you didn't choose it! I know that!

333
00:20:08,749 --> 00:20:11,919
But you can't keep hiding from the world
and being sad about it forever!

334
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:14,588
- Now, get in there!
- What do you know? Leave me alone!

335
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,256
No! Stop!

336
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:18,383
Open the door! Hey!

337
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,135
Ah, come on… Hey!

338
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,054
- [banging on door]
- Kaho! Kaho? Please.

339
00:20:22,137 --> 00:20:24,181
Is that what you wanna hear?
I'm begging you!

340
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:26,642
Okay? Could you please do it?
Could you please?

341
00:20:27,184 --> 00:20:28,018
Open up!

342
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:30,145
[upbeat dance music playing inside]

343
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:34,650
FUJITA FUJIKAWA

344
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:38,111
<i>Ah, welcome!</i>

345
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:40,572
[upbeat dance music continues]

346
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:42,991
[lively chatter and cheering inside]

347
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:48,830
- Is… is Kenta free?
- Kenta's with someone at the moment.

348
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:52,709
In the meantime, we can offer you a table
so you can wait for him, if you'd like?

349
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,545
Okay, sure.

350
00:20:56,046 --> 00:20:57,547
Great! Right this way.

351
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:01,635
We have a customer coming in.

352
00:21:01,718 --> 00:21:03,387
[hosts] Welcome!

353
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:12,729
[Fujita] <i>Kaho.</i>

354
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:14,606
Kaho?

355
00:21:15,524 --> 00:21:16,566
Can you hear me?

356
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:21,029
<i>If you can hear me, say something.</i>
<i>Are you okay in there?</i>

357
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:22,990
<i>Wait, was that Mimi?</i>

358
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:24,616
<i>That was Mimi!</i>

359
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:26,827
That was Mimi, wasn't it?

360
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:28,578
Kaho?

361
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:31,748
[host] Here you are.
It'll just be a moment.

362
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:34,251
[Fujita] <i>Can you hear me? Are you okay?</i>

363
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:37,254
[quietly] Yeah, it's cool.
I'll figure something out.

364
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:42,801
I can confirm that Kenta is
on the other side of the room.

365
00:21:42,884 --> 00:21:44,303
[Fujita] <i>Seriously? Call him over!</i>

366
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:45,887
[man] It's okay, don't worry.

367
00:21:46,388 --> 00:21:47,639
[Mimi laughs]

368
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:50,392
- [man 2] Another round!
- [people cheering]

369
00:21:52,644 --> 00:21:54,813
- [people chanting]
- [cork pops]

370
00:21:57,649 --> 00:21:59,985
[chanting]

371
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:04,323
[dream-like music playing]

372
00:22:04,406 --> 00:22:07,534
- [hosts] Drink it down, keep it up!
- [people laughing]

373
00:22:07,617 --> 00:22:09,202
[indistinct chattering]

374
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:11,955
[hosts] Chug! Chug! Chug! Chug!

375
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:15,000
- [host 1] A round of applause!
- [woman 1] Hell, yeah!

376
00:22:16,376 --> 00:22:19,629
- [host 2] Whoa, hang on. You okay?
- [woman 2 laughs] You hang on!

377
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:23,842
- [dream-like music continues]
- [indistinct chatter and laughing]

378
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:26,136
[man] Excuse me.

379
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:30,599
- Excuse me, miss?
- [music fades]

380
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:33,518
I'd like to make this a night to remember.

381
00:22:34,102 --> 00:22:35,604
How does that sound to you?

382
00:22:36,104 --> 00:22:38,148
Pleasure to meet you. My name's Kenta.

383
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:40,067
Welcome to my world.

384
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:42,778
[soft, quirky music playing]

385
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:44,446
KENTA SUMERAGI

386
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:45,697
<i>May I sit with you?</i>

387
00:22:47,908 --> 00:22:50,911
Nice and easy. Don't ask anything
that could give away the game.

388
00:22:50,994 --> 00:22:52,746
<i>Just set the mood.</i>

389
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:57,125
Uh, so, uh…

390
00:22:58,251 --> 00:23:00,462
I… I don't…

391
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:02,672
- It's dark in here.
- Yeah. Sorry?

392
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:04,883
Why don't I take those off?

393
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:06,802
- No, no.
- [Kenta] Hey, it's okay.

394
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,388
Sh, sh.

395
00:23:09,471 --> 00:23:10,680
[Kaho] No, I just…

396
00:23:11,723 --> 00:23:14,643
[Kenta] Sh, sh, sh, sh.

397
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:17,396
[shushing softly]

398
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:22,317
[Kaho whimpers softly]

399
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:25,987
[Kaho groans]

400
00:23:26,947 --> 00:23:29,032
You have such beautiful eyes.

401
00:23:29,533 --> 00:23:30,909
Why would you hide them?

402
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:34,121
Careful now.

403
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:36,873
That's just him trying to butter you up.

404
00:23:36,957 --> 00:23:38,250
Cheers then, miss!

405
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:40,335
[glasses clink]

406
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:52,597
Kaho, that's alcohol.

407
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,266
Probably strong.

408
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,185
<i>Slow down. It's alcoholic.</i>

409
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,313
<i>Don't drink the whole thing. Just…</i>

410
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:01,690
[Fujita sighs]

411
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,942
- [Kaho] Mm.
- [Kenta chuckles]

412
00:24:04,526 --> 00:24:06,862
Whoa. Nice. You want another?

413
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:10,907
Yeah.

414
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:14,369
[clicks fingers]

415
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,038
[Kaho chuckles]

416
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:18,623
[Kenta clicks tongue]

417
00:24:18,707 --> 00:24:21,042
- [Kaho giggles]
- [clicks tongue]

418
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,295
Kaho, you okay?

419
00:24:23,378 --> 00:24:25,547
The mood's probably good now.
Let's ask him.

420
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:31,136
- For you.
- Uh, thanks. [chuckles]

421
00:24:31,219 --> 00:24:32,053
Yeah, thanks.

422
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:34,306
- I'll take another glass, actually.
- Of course.

423
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:36,725
[Fujita] <i>You've had enough.</i>
<i>You don't need any more.</i>

424
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:38,977
Yeah, I know! Shush!

425
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,645
Hmm? What was that?

426
00:24:41,563 --> 00:24:42,856
Oh, uh…

427
00:24:42,939 --> 00:24:44,691
- It was nothing.
- Hmm.

428
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:49,404
I can't figure out why you'd wanna know
where that abandoned building is.

429
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:51,948
- You shooting a movie?
- No, a movie?

430
00:24:52,032 --> 00:24:54,451
- [Kaho] <i>I mean… Kinda.</i>
- Wait. Yeah, yeah, okay.

431
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:57,412
We've got big plans
to shoot a horror movie.

432
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:58,788
[Kaho] Yeah, we've got

433
00:24:59,664 --> 00:25:01,708
really big plans to film a horror movie.

434
00:25:01,791 --> 00:25:03,376
[Fujita] <i>In the movie, there's an idol…</i>

435
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:06,588
There's an idol who comes back
from the dead as a vengeful spirit.

436
00:25:06,671 --> 00:25:08,548
<i>- Kills other idols…</i>
- And then she, like…

437
00:25:08,632 --> 00:25:12,719
Uh… She kills people,
she kills more popular idols, one by one.

438
00:25:12,802 --> 00:25:13,929
Uh, hey,

439
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:16,848
do you, like, need more actors?

440
00:25:16,932 --> 00:25:19,851
It's just that the whole reason
I got into this in the first place

441
00:25:19,935 --> 00:25:21,061
was to be an actor.

442
00:25:21,144 --> 00:25:23,271
- I work here for now, but…
- [Fujita] <i>Manager.</i>

443
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:24,981
- Well…
- <i>We're looking for a manager.</i>

444
00:25:25,065 --> 00:25:28,276
We do need a new manager.

445
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:31,613
Like, someone to play him. The manager.

446
00:25:32,113 --> 00:25:34,866
- I think you'd be perfect for it.
- You think so? Really?

447
00:25:35,492 --> 00:25:38,620
The movie opens on a wide shot
of the abandoned warehouse.

448
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,997
And then, a ways away, we see her…

449
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:43,041
The ghost of the dead idol.

450
00:25:43,124 --> 00:25:45,460
The new girl group is coming.

451
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:47,754
They're shooting a music video
at the warehouse,

452
00:25:47,837 --> 00:25:50,799
and they don't notice anything
out of the ordinary.

453
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:53,718
Until our girl group's manager,

454
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:57,222
who was just helping out on set,
all of a sudden…

455
00:25:57,305 --> 00:26:00,684
All of a sudden,
he feels a damp, clammy, cold hand--

456
00:26:00,767 --> 00:26:01,851
Wait, wait, stop.

457
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:04,938
You said it opened on the group
arriving at the warehouse?

458
00:26:05,021 --> 00:26:06,690
- Then…
- [Kaho] Hmm?

459
00:26:07,190 --> 00:26:10,610
Nobody quite knew why, but that day,
there was a chill in the air…

460
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:12,821
[eerie music playing]

461
00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:19,536
[Kenta] <i>There's an old abandoned factory</i>
<i>in Katsushika. I think it's still there.</i>

462
00:26:21,204 --> 00:26:24,708
<i>It's funny, ever since I was a kid,</i>
<i>people had talked about it being haunted,</i>

463
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:27,669
<i>so I always stayed away. Until that day.</i>

464
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:30,088
[Kenta] Okay, ladies, we're here.
Everyone out.

465
00:26:30,171 --> 00:26:32,465
Hey! We might have to leave.
Keep the van running.

466
00:26:32,549 --> 00:26:33,466
- Tenga!
- Sir?

467
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:36,469
If anyone asks, you tell them
you're with the Tokyo Film School.

468
00:26:36,553 --> 00:26:38,221
- You hear me?
- [Tenga] Yes, Mr. Goro.

469
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:42,434
[Kenta] <i>It was the perfect location</i>
<i>for the shoot, so I recommended we use it.</i>

470
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:44,394
[wind whistling]

471
00:26:44,477 --> 00:26:46,688
[Kenta] <i>It's hard</i>
<i>to put into words, honestly,</i>

472
00:26:47,897 --> 00:26:50,108
<i>but there was something about that place.</i>

473
00:26:50,191 --> 00:26:51,776
<i>Something… wrong.</i>

474
00:26:53,194 --> 00:26:56,865
<i>And then, we were just about to start</i>
<i>shooting at the back of the lot…</i>

475
00:26:57,866 --> 00:26:58,700
There.

476
00:26:59,659 --> 00:27:00,952
Hey, I got that.

477
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:03,288
Uh, Kenta…

478
00:27:03,872 --> 00:27:06,791
I don't wanna be here. I'm scared.

479
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:09,919
Can you give me a hug?

480
00:27:10,629 --> 00:27:13,173
- No, I can't give you a hug here.
- Why not?

481
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:15,508
I'm really scared.

482
00:27:24,684 --> 00:27:25,560
[Kenta grunts]

483
00:27:28,188 --> 00:27:29,773
[Mimi laughs]

484
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:36,821
Anna.

485
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:40,158
You know I don't like waiting.

486
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:42,035
Mimi, pull yourself together.

487
00:27:42,869 --> 00:27:44,788
You know idols aren't allowed to date.

488
00:27:52,796 --> 00:27:54,297
And action, action!

489
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:56,758
These six devils will haunt your dreams
tonight!

490
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:58,510
- Miho!
- Mai!

491
00:27:58,593 --> 00:28:00,053
- Mimi!
- Ayaka!

492
00:28:00,136 --> 00:28:02,013
- Yuri!
- Anna!

493
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:04,265
[together] Dream Succubus!

494
00:28:08,144 --> 00:28:09,688
[music starts]

495
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:11,773
[gothic pop music playing]

496
00:28:11,856 --> 00:28:13,858
[lyrics in Japanese]

497
00:28:17,779 --> 00:28:20,573
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

498
00:28:21,157 --> 00:28:22,617
<i>♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

499
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:24,703
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

500
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,289
<i>♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

501
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:30,375
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

502
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:34,462
[lyrics in Japanese]

503
00:28:36,673 --> 00:28:38,091
What? What's the matter?

504
00:28:39,843 --> 00:28:42,387
You forgot the choreography. Again! Kenta!

505
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:44,764
- On it!
- [Goro] First positions! Starting again!

506
00:28:44,848 --> 00:28:45,890
[sighs] What's wrong?

507
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:47,600
- Kenta.
- Yeah?

508
00:28:48,643 --> 00:28:49,477
Look.

509
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,563
[eerie, suspenseful music playing]

510
00:29:01,614 --> 00:29:04,409
What are you looking at?
Is there something there?

511
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:07,370
No. It's nothing.

512
00:29:08,329 --> 00:29:11,124
[Goro] Good. Back to one!
I wanna get this in one take!

513
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:13,376
[woman] Places, everyone! Let's go!

514
00:29:13,460 --> 00:29:15,920
[Kenta] <i>It wasn't nothing. I saw it too.</i>

515
00:29:17,005 --> 00:29:20,633
<i>But I explained it away at the time.</i>
<i>Thought I was just imagining things.</i>

516
00:29:21,634 --> 00:29:24,512
But then I saw the finished music video,
and I knew…

517
00:29:25,638 --> 00:29:27,390
[Mimi laughs]

518
00:29:28,016 --> 00:29:30,143
- [man] Come on…
- Oh, Leo…

519
00:29:30,226 --> 00:29:32,979
- I love your skin. It's so pretty.
- [Leo] Smooth, right?

520
00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:35,482
- [Leo] I've got a new skincare routine.
- Ah, you're cute!

521
00:29:35,565 --> 00:29:38,401
- Look at you!
- [Leo] Okay, hands off the face now.

522
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:39,903
[Leo] That's enough!

523
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:42,530
[Kenta sighs]
We all had a lot of fun… before…

524
00:29:46,701 --> 00:29:48,912
Mm… Mm-hmm.

525
00:29:51,164 --> 00:29:52,290
[gags]

526
00:29:52,373 --> 00:29:53,958
Whoa! Hey! You okay?

527
00:29:54,042 --> 00:29:55,710
You okay? You gonna puke?

528
00:29:56,419 --> 00:29:57,545
- You all right?
- [slurps]

529
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:59,255
Yeah? Hey.

530
00:29:59,339 --> 00:30:00,465
- [Kaho gulps]
- You okay?

531
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:02,050
- Yeah, all good.
- Right.

532
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:06,679
[Kaho gags]

533
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:10,975
- [gags]
- Oh, whoa!

534
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:14,145
[Fujita] Ah, ah, ah, ah, ah!

535
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:17,315
[sighs] I told you not to drink so much.

536
00:30:17,398 --> 00:30:19,025
You know how much that puke cost?

537
00:30:19,108 --> 00:30:20,443
[Kaho] Please shut up.

538
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:24,823
[coughs] Whatever.
We got the address, didn't we?

539
00:30:24,906 --> 00:30:26,866
Once we tell Dadashow, we get paid.

540
00:30:27,367 --> 00:30:29,702
- If they're telling the truth.
- So it was worth it.

541
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:31,830
[Fujita] Katsushika Ward, Tateishi Kita--

542
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:33,790
- We're not going there now?
- Obviously.

543
00:30:33,873 --> 00:30:36,042
[Kaho] No! You can't make me!

544
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,752
- I wanna go home.
- Get in the van.

545
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:40,338
- I wanna have a bath, I stink.
- Trust me, I know.

546
00:30:40,421 --> 00:30:42,465
- I'm tired. My head hurts.
- Okay, got it.

547
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:47,762
- I don't feel good. Hmm.
- Okay, directions.

548
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:52,141
As soon as we have the money,

549
00:30:52,225 --> 00:30:54,519
you can get that treatment
you always wanted.

550
00:30:57,230 --> 00:30:58,439
[Fujita whistles]

551
00:31:00,024 --> 00:31:01,150
[Kaho chuckles]

552
00:31:02,193 --> 00:31:04,821
Okay. Thanks, bro.

553
00:31:07,323 --> 00:31:09,242
Okay, well in that case…

554
00:31:10,493 --> 00:31:12,161
I guess I'll be on camera too.

555
00:31:12,245 --> 00:31:15,248
What? For the live streams?
You wanna host?

556
00:31:15,331 --> 00:31:16,583
- You changed your mind?
- Quit it.

557
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:17,750
- Awesome!
- No. Hey!

558
00:31:17,834 --> 00:31:19,919
- You're gonna host? Hell yeah!
- [Kaho laughs]

559
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:22,213
- Great day for believers!
- [Kaho groans]

560
00:31:22,797 --> 00:31:24,757
Great day for believers!

561
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:26,467
- All right!
- You're so loud. My head.

562
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:29,137
[Fujita] We're gonna have
a million subscribers, baby!

563
00:31:29,220 --> 00:31:31,472
[Kaho] Yo, could you--
I'm gonna puke. Slow down!

564
00:31:31,556 --> 00:31:33,892
[haunting music playing]

565
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:44,819
This is the creepiest place.

566
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:48,114
Let's just get what we need
and get outta here.

567
00:31:56,581 --> 00:31:59,250
[Fujita] Hey! Kaho, check it out!

568
00:31:59,959 --> 00:32:01,252
[Kaho] What? Where?

569
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:04,339
[haunting music continues]

570
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:09,469
[Fujita] <i>Is that the window?</i>

571
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:14,098
- [Kaho] <i>Is it? Looks right to me.</i>
- [Fujita] <i>No, not the one.</i>

572
00:32:16,476 --> 00:32:18,561
<i>We're looking for a blue door.</i>

573
00:32:25,068 --> 00:32:26,694
[wind whistling]

574
00:32:26,778 --> 00:32:28,488
Fujita, Fujita.

575
00:32:28,571 --> 00:32:29,530
[Fujita] Uh?

576
00:32:30,823 --> 00:32:31,866
Look, right there.

577
00:32:33,576 --> 00:32:36,329
- That's the one. That's the blue door.
- Yeah.

578
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:41,250
[Fujita gasps] Here it is.

579
00:32:45,254 --> 00:32:46,589
[Kaho] Okay…

580
00:32:49,425 --> 00:32:51,177
[wind whistling]

581
00:32:51,260 --> 00:32:53,471
[haunting music continues]

582
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:03,064
[breathing shakily]

583
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:09,028
- [clattering]
- [Kaho] Let's not mess around.

584
00:33:09,112 --> 00:33:11,239
[Fujita] We need to get more lights on.

585
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:14,242
- [Kaho] What?
- [Fujita] J… just find a light switch.

586
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:16,285
Wait, are you scared?

587
00:33:20,289 --> 00:33:22,291
I've made peace with my fear, so…

588
00:33:22,375 --> 00:33:24,711
That's why I'm a true horror connoisseur.

589
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:26,796
[Kaho] What does that mean?

590
00:33:36,806 --> 00:33:38,558
- [switch clicks]
- [Fujita] Are you doing that?

591
00:33:38,641 --> 00:33:39,475
- [Kaho] No.
- What?

592
00:33:40,226 --> 00:33:42,478
Who turned the lights on? What happened?

593
00:33:43,730 --> 00:33:45,440
What if someone lives here?

594
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:47,150
There's no way.

595
00:33:47,650 --> 00:33:48,735
Unless it's him?

596
00:33:48,818 --> 00:33:51,821
The Human Vapor isn't going to pay
the electric bill every month.

597
00:33:51,904 --> 00:33:53,156
Right, yeah.

598
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:57,452
[Kaho] Whoa.

599
00:34:02,999 --> 00:34:05,168
- Fujita! Look!
- What?

600
00:34:05,251 --> 00:34:06,461
- Down here.
- What is it?

601
00:34:18,723 --> 00:34:21,392
- [Kaho] Uh…
- [Fujita] Where do you think it goes?

602
00:34:21,934 --> 00:34:23,686
[water dripping]

603
00:34:23,770 --> 00:34:25,897
[eerie music playing]

604
00:34:31,277 --> 00:34:32,153
Right.

605
00:34:33,696 --> 00:34:34,947
Come on, let's go.

606
00:34:35,448 --> 00:34:37,075
[Fujita grunting]

607
00:34:37,158 --> 00:34:39,160
[eerie music continues]

608
00:34:43,664 --> 00:34:46,084
- [Fujita] What is this place?
- [Kaho grunts]

609
00:34:47,043 --> 00:34:48,127
[Fujita] Whoa.

610
00:34:50,088 --> 00:34:52,090
[door rattling]

611
00:34:54,300 --> 00:34:55,551
<i>What's over there?</i>

612
00:34:59,430 --> 00:35:01,432
[music fades out]

613
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:12,860
[yelps] <i>There's something there! It's him!</i>

614
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:14,028
[Kaho] <i>What the hell?</i>

615
00:35:16,405 --> 00:35:17,990
- [Kaho] <i>It's just a cat.</i>
- [Fujita] <i>Oh.</i>

616
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:19,033
[cat meows]

617
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:21,285
[breathing shakily]

618
00:35:24,831 --> 00:35:27,166
[Kaho] What are you doing
all the way down here?

619
00:35:27,708 --> 00:35:28,709
[Fujita sniffs]

620
00:35:28,793 --> 00:35:30,586
[water dripping]

621
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:33,089
[suspenseful music playing]

622
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:36,509
Fujita, look.

623
00:35:38,594 --> 00:35:40,012
We can get through here.

624
00:35:40,096 --> 00:35:41,139
Okay?

625
00:35:43,516 --> 00:35:45,268
[Kaho grunting]

626
00:35:46,102 --> 00:35:47,812
[Fujita grunting]

627
00:36:06,914 --> 00:36:10,376
RECORDING

628
00:36:10,459 --> 00:36:13,296
- I… I think something's there.
- [Fujita] What?

629
00:36:14,255 --> 00:36:16,299
- Where?
- Look, look, look, there.

630
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:27,768
[Kaho] Fujita?

631
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,605
What is it? Fujita?

632
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,151
- Kaho.
- Yeah?

633
00:36:35,234 --> 00:36:36,110
Look.

634
00:36:38,029 --> 00:36:39,071
Hold this.

635
00:36:39,739 --> 00:36:41,741
[suspenseful music building]

636
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:48,581
What?

637
00:36:51,209 --> 00:36:53,002
The Human Vapor.

638
00:36:55,546 --> 00:36:56,923
You think it's him?

639
00:36:57,506 --> 00:36:59,258
It has to be. Look at it.

640
00:36:59,967 --> 00:37:01,177
Just look…

641
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:05,306
[Kaho] Why isn't he moving?

642
00:37:05,389 --> 00:37:07,058
[Fujita] He must be asleep.

643
00:37:07,808 --> 00:37:09,477
[Kaho] What do you mean, asleep?

644
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:11,520
Whoa…

645
00:37:15,566 --> 00:37:16,984
CALLING DADASHOW

646
00:37:17,068 --> 00:37:19,528
[Kaho breathes deeply]

647
00:37:19,612 --> 00:37:21,822
[wind whistling]

648
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:25,368
[automated voice] <i>The customer</i>
<i>you have dialed is not available…</i>

649
00:37:25,451 --> 00:37:26,953
They're not answering.

650
00:37:27,036 --> 00:37:29,997
- <i>If you wish to leave a message</i>…
- Leave a message then.

651
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,419
Hi, this is a message for Dadashow.

652
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:38,005
This is Kaho, from the <i>Terror Zone.</i>

653
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:40,299
I can tell you
where the abandoned building is.

654
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:42,802
I even took some videos at the site, so…

655
00:37:42,885 --> 00:37:45,137
Call me back, please.
The sooner the better.

656
00:37:45,221 --> 00:37:46,555
- Thank--
- [phone ringing]

657
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:48,599
[phone ringing]

658
00:37:48,683 --> 00:37:49,809
What? [grunts]

659
00:37:49,892 --> 00:37:51,269
- [zipping]
- What's going on?

660
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:53,312
- [Kaho] Uh…
- [Fujita] What's going on?

661
00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:55,147
- [Kaho] There!
- [Fujita] What? Stop it!

662
00:37:55,231 --> 00:37:58,025
- [Kaho] W… what's it doing?
- [Fujita] What is this?

663
00:37:58,776 --> 00:37:59,902
- [Kaho] Look!
- [yelps]

664
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:02,029
- [Kaho] What? What are those?
- [Fujita] Dominoes?

665
00:38:02,113 --> 00:38:04,573
- [Kaho] Did someone set a trap?
- [Fujita] Record player?

666
00:38:04,657 --> 00:38:06,117
[Fujita] No, don't touch it!

667
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:08,786
- [Kaho] What do we do?
- [Fujita] I don't know! Wait…

668
00:38:08,869 --> 00:38:11,205
- [Fujita] Is that… music?
- [record crackling]

669
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:13,291
- [Fujita] What?
- [Kaho] Wait a second.

670
00:38:13,374 --> 00:38:15,710
["Ellie My Love"
by Southern All Stars playing]

671
00:38:17,336 --> 00:38:18,212
[Kaho grunts]

672
00:38:19,088 --> 00:38:20,631
[Fujita] Hide! We gotta hide!

673
00:38:20,715 --> 00:38:22,591
- [Kaho] But where?
- [Fujita] Down there!

674
00:38:22,675 --> 00:38:24,927
[Kaho panting]

675
00:38:25,511 --> 00:38:27,513
["Ellie My Love" continues playing]

676
00:38:27,596 --> 00:38:29,598
[lyrics in Japanese]

677
00:38:33,019 --> 00:38:34,812
Do you know what this song is?

678
00:38:35,354 --> 00:38:36,856
- "Ellie My Love."
- Who's Ellie?

679
00:38:37,523 --> 00:38:39,525
[Fujita] It's a song
by Southern All Stars.

680
00:38:40,443 --> 00:38:42,403
I think it came out before you were born.

681
00:38:46,907 --> 00:38:48,367
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

682
00:38:48,451 --> 00:38:50,244
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

683
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:53,122
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

684
00:38:53,956 --> 00:38:55,958
[lyrics in Japanese]

685
00:39:14,643 --> 00:39:16,020
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

686
00:39:16,103 --> 00:39:17,772
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

687
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:20,816
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

688
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:22,902
[lyrics in Japanese]

689
00:39:41,837 --> 00:39:43,631
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

690
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:45,383
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

691
00:39:45,466 --> 00:39:48,511
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

692
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,554
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

693
00:39:50,638 --> 00:39:52,098
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

694
00:39:52,181 --> 00:39:55,684
<i>♪ So sweet… ♪</i>

695
00:40:08,197 --> 00:40:09,949
Greetings, listener.

696
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:12,368
Go right ahead

697
00:40:13,285 --> 00:40:15,121
and make a wish.

698
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:17,581
[modem connecting tone]

699
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:19,583
["Ellie My Love" continues]

700
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,002
[Kaho gasps softly]

701
00:40:23,003 --> 00:40:25,423
[automated voice]
<i>Your target is Saburo Otomo.</i>

702
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:27,091
<i>I just faxed you the details.</i>

703
00:40:27,174 --> 00:40:29,218
<i>Kill him immediately.</i>

704
00:40:29,301 --> 00:40:32,680
- [whispers] What did he say?
- He's gonna go kill a guy.

705
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:34,765
["Ellie My Love" continues]

706
00:40:44,942 --> 00:40:46,360
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

707
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:48,112
<i>- ♪ My love… ♪</i>
- [door opening]

708
00:40:48,195 --> 00:40:51,031
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

709
00:40:55,911 --> 00:40:57,079
[quietly] Fujita, no!

710
00:40:57,580 --> 00:40:59,165
It's dangerous! Don't go.

711
00:40:59,248 --> 00:41:00,207
No, stop! Don't!

712
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:02,668
You'll get yourself killed! Fujita!

713
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:14,430
<i>- ♪ Ellie, my love… ♪</i>
- [song fades out]

714
00:41:17,099 --> 00:41:18,100
[record player clicks]

715
00:41:28,861 --> 00:41:31,447
[tense, sinister music playing]

716
00:41:45,127 --> 00:41:47,296
[exhales] What the hell was that?

717
00:41:47,796 --> 00:41:49,131
What just happened?

718
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:54,678
[Fujita] I think

719
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:58,390
that song that was just playing

720
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:01,227
must be some sort of trigger.

721
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,813
Wait, so,

722
00:42:04,897 --> 00:42:07,441
when this specific song is played he…

723
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:10,152
he… what? Turns into a human?

724
00:42:10,236 --> 00:42:11,904
[Fujita] Exactly, and then

725
00:42:12,571 --> 00:42:14,448
his orders print out over there,

726
00:42:14,949 --> 00:42:16,200
and he carries them out.

727
00:42:17,618 --> 00:42:20,496
So what you're saying is…
That's impossible.

728
00:42:22,206 --> 00:42:24,875
I'm saying the Human Vapor
is being mind controlled.

729
00:42:26,544 --> 00:42:27,586
He's not

730
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:30,422
acting of his own free will.

731
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:36,220
[Fujita grunting]

732
00:42:38,806 --> 00:42:40,182
Hey, Fujita.

733
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:43,060
- Should we be telling someone?
- [Fujita] Telling them what?

734
00:42:43,143 --> 00:42:45,729
That the Human Vapor's got another target.

735
00:42:46,272 --> 00:42:49,483
If we call the police now, we might
be able to stop him killing again.

736
00:42:49,567 --> 00:42:53,445
Stop him? No way.
No, no, no, no. Hey, listen.

737
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:55,573
- Hey. We're not gonna call.
- [Kaho] What?

738
00:42:55,656 --> 00:42:57,491
We're gonna take it up a notch!

739
00:42:57,575 --> 00:43:00,995
We need to get videos of the puppeteer
controlling the Human Vapor.

740
00:43:01,078 --> 00:43:02,788
Just think what that would be worth.

741
00:43:02,871 --> 00:43:05,416
We could get way more
than they promised at first.

742
00:43:06,375 --> 00:43:09,420
- Isn't that kinda dangerous?
- [Fujita] Ah, it'll be fine.

743
00:43:09,503 --> 00:43:11,880
We go in, we get it done.

744
00:43:12,756 --> 00:43:14,842
You and I, we're gonna get paid,

745
00:43:14,925 --> 00:43:16,302
show off our prize,

746
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:19,847
then turn our backs on this town
and leave it behind!

747
00:43:21,515 --> 00:43:22,725
Gross, dude. [laughs]

748
00:43:22,808 --> 00:43:24,935
[laughs] Bleh.

749
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:26,228
- [Kaho] I just…
- What?

750
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:30,190
I don't know, you make it sound
like our lives are awful, but they're not.

751
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:34,653
[Fujita sighs]

752
00:43:34,737 --> 00:43:37,031
That's your opinion, but I don't agree.

753
00:43:37,615 --> 00:43:40,034
[cigarette lighter striking repeatedly]

754
00:43:48,584 --> 00:43:50,002
Okay.

755
00:43:52,796 --> 00:43:54,590
[newscaster] <i>Shortly after 7:30,</i>

756
00:43:54,673 --> 00:43:57,635
<i>police received reports of a car</i>
<i>being attacked by the Human Vapor…</i>

757
00:43:57,718 --> 00:44:00,262
We gotta get back to the factory now,
beat him there.

758
00:44:00,346 --> 00:44:01,430
Fujita, look.

759
00:44:01,513 --> 00:44:03,891
[newscaster] <i>According to</i>
<i>the Metropolitan Police,</i>

760
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:06,352
<i>the victim was Mr. Saburo Otomo,</i>

761
00:44:06,435 --> 00:44:08,687
<i>president of the Fujishiro Syndicate.</i>

762
00:44:08,771 --> 00:44:12,816
<i>Mr. Otomo was rushed to a nearby hospital,</i>
<i>but was pronounced dead on arrival.</i>

763
00:44:13,984 --> 00:44:16,570
<i>- Receiving reports that the Human Vapor…</i>
- Oh my God.

764
00:44:16,654 --> 00:44:18,197
<i>…first attacked him at work.</i>

765
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:22,034
<i>He managed to escape in his car,</i>
<i>but was pursued by the Human Vapor…</i>

766
00:44:22,117 --> 00:44:24,119
[whooshing]

767
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:27,122
- Go, go, go!
- [Kaho whimpers]

768
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:30,042
[dramatic music playing]

769
00:44:32,294 --> 00:44:34,046
[Kaho grunting]

770
00:44:34,129 --> 00:44:35,464
[Fujita] Hurry! Come on!

771
00:45:04,284 --> 00:45:06,745
He's turning back into a statue.

772
00:45:08,747 --> 00:45:09,832
[Fujita] Oh shit.

773
00:45:11,583 --> 00:45:13,168
This is so crazy.

774
00:45:14,962 --> 00:45:19,174
So, if someone is controlling him,
why does he come all the way back here?

775
00:45:19,258 --> 00:45:20,259
[Fujita grunts]

776
00:45:21,301 --> 00:45:23,762
I bet this is like his respawn point,
you know?

777
00:45:24,263 --> 00:45:26,432
- "Respawn"?
- It's a video game thing.

778
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:27,641
It's where he starts.

779
00:45:28,434 --> 00:45:31,061
Maybe he's programmed
to go back to that spot.

780
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:33,772
[clanging and footsteps]

781
00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:35,190
[music builds then fades]

782
00:45:35,274 --> 00:45:36,108
Uh?

783
00:45:37,151 --> 00:45:38,193
Who's that?

784
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:43,240
[Fujita] It can't be a coincidence.
It's gotta be the person controlling him.

785
00:45:44,742 --> 00:45:46,160
[footsteps approaching]

786
00:45:46,243 --> 00:45:48,996
- [Kaho] They're coming.
- [Fujita] Quick! In here!

787
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:55,669
[Kaho] What are you doing?! Hey!

788
00:46:04,052 --> 00:46:06,054
[tense music droning]

789
00:46:08,974 --> 00:46:10,350
[phone vibrating]

790
00:46:10,434 --> 00:46:12,603
[Fujita] Sh! Turn it off!
Turn it off, quick!

791
00:46:13,103 --> 00:46:14,313
[Kaho whimpers]

792
00:46:14,897 --> 00:46:16,648
- [Kaho] It's Dadashow.
- Who cares? Hang up!

793
00:46:16,732 --> 00:46:17,733
[door clatters]

794
00:46:17,816 --> 00:46:19,818
[phone continues vibrating]

795
00:46:21,695 --> 00:46:22,988
[vibrating stops]

796
00:46:23,614 --> 00:46:25,574
[woman] Kaho from <i>Terror Zone</i>. Here I am.

797
00:46:27,284 --> 00:46:29,161
You said the sooner the better.

798
00:46:29,244 --> 00:46:30,788
[intriguing music playing]

799
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:33,874
[music fades]

800
00:46:37,628 --> 00:46:40,088
["Wagamama Nightmare"
by Dream Succubus playing]

801
00:46:40,172 --> 00:46:42,174
[lyrics in Japanese]

802
00:46:46,220 --> 00:46:48,472
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

803
00:46:48,555 --> 00:46:49,473
DREAM SUCCUBUS

804
00:46:49,556 --> 00:46:50,766
<i>♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

805
00:46:50,849 --> 00:46:52,601
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

806
00:46:55,020 --> 00:46:56,438
<i>♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

807
00:46:56,522 --> 00:46:58,148
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

808
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:02,402
[song continues in Japanese]

809
00:47:40,274 --> 00:47:41,483
WALK QUIETLY IN THE HALLWAY

810
00:48:07,926 --> 00:48:09,511
<i>♪ Nightmare ♪</i>

811
00:48:10,012 --> 00:48:12,180
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

812
00:48:12,264 --> 00:48:13,640
<i>- ♪ Uh-huh ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

813
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:15,726
<i>- ♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Ooh! ♪</i>

814
00:48:17,895 --> 00:48:19,396
<i>♪ Dream Succubus ♪</i>

815
00:48:19,479 --> 00:48:21,481
<i>♪ Wagamama nightmare ♪</i>

816
00:48:24,026 --> 00:48:26,111
[lyrics in Japanese]

817
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:10,989
♪ <i>Wagamama nightmare, ah-ah ♪</i>

818
00:50:04,918 --> 00:50:07,379
♪ <i>Wagamama nightmare, ah-ah ♪</i>

819
00:50:07,462 --> 00:50:09,464
[men screaming]

820
00:50:09,548 --> 00:50:13,760
WAGAMAMA NIGHTMARE

821
00:50:14,678 --> 00:50:17,639
[all, distorted] These six devils
will haunt your dreams tonight!

822
00:50:17,723 --> 00:50:19,433
- Miho!
- Mai!

823
00:50:19,516 --> 00:50:21,184
- Mimi!
- Ayaka!

824
00:50:21,268 --> 00:50:23,145
- Yuri!
- Anna!

825
00:50:23,729 --> 00:50:25,564
[together] Dream Succubus!

826
00:50:25,647 --> 00:50:27,274
[music ends]
